article.description: Collinsworth has triple-double, BYU tops USF 99-68
article.headline: Collinsworth has triple-double, BYU tops USF 99-68
article.linkText: Collinsworth has triple-double, BYU tops USF 99-68
article.story: SAN FRANCISCO -- Kyle Collinsworth had his third triple-double of the season and Brigham Young beat San Francisco 99-68 Saturday night. Collinsworth had 12 points, 12 rebounds and 10 assists for BYU (13-4, 3-1 West Coast Conference). When Collinsworth left the game he had nine assists but was credited with a tenth after further review. The junior needs one more triple-double to tie the NCAA Division I season record held by Michael Anderson (1986), Brian Shaw (1988), Jason Kidd (1994) and Stephane Lasme (2007). BYU led by 30 before Devin Watson's free throws for San Francisco (7-9, 1-3) made it 57-29 at halftime. Tyler Haws scored 22, Chase Fischer added 20, Anson Winder 17 and Jake Toolson 11 for the Cougars. Those four together shot 15 of 23 from 3-point range. Kruize Pinkins led the Dons with 15 points. Devin Watson scored 13, Mark Tollefsen added 12 and Tim Derksen 11.
